parser

Class DateParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • parser.DateParser

  • public class DateParser
extends java.lang.Object
    This class focuses on breaking down a string for date into the relevant components it takes in a date input with varying degree of flexibility, in dd/mm/yy or number-month-year format.
    Author:
    sylvesterchin

      • processDate

        private void processDate(java.lang.String input)
                  throws java.lang.Exception
        This method further processes the input from date-time-parser. format types include 1. dd-Month-yyyy format: 3rd june 2013 2. ddmmyyy format: 4/5-5/6 3. relative date format: next monday
        Parameters:
        input - date input from user, not null.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
